<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0556 </DOCNO><TEXT>We present a description of the construction of two variants of the hollow-cathodeion source that have been developed to separate small amounts of radioactiveisotopes at the JASNAPP-2 isotope separator on-line facility. A limitedreview of the source characteristics is given.</TEXT></DOC>